<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880707-0067 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Zurn Industries Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> ZRN </CO><TEXT>   Zurn Industries Inc. said its National Energy Production Corp. subsidiary received a $35 million contract to build a waste-to-energy power plant for Imperial Resource Recovery Associates L.P.    Zurn, Erie, Pa., said the new 15,000-kilowatt biomass-fired power plant will be near the U.S.-Mexican border at Brawley, Calif. It expects to begin construction in October and should complete the project by January 1990.    Zurn, which designs and makes environmental waste-to-energy systems, water controls and other technologies, said electricity produced by the plant will be sold to Southern California Edison Co. </TEXT></DOC>